I'm going to see if there is a AC cap by logging some damage versus AC.<br><br>Please read through my plan and post if you think I need to modify something to make it fair.<br><br><br>Details<br><br>Before each fight:<br>0. base 120 agility<br>1. I'll get an agility buff from a shaman.  +57 agil<br>2. I'll use my primal LS until it procs and grants me 255 agility. +100agil<br><br>I'll repeat each AC test 3 times.<br><br>I'll increase my AC in increments until I've gone as high as I can.<br><br>I'll stand facing the monk to allow ripostes dodging etc.<br><br>I'll divide my total hitpoints by the time it took to kill me.<br><br>This ratio should come out as a damage per second.<br><br>I'll then plot the damage per second against an increasing scale of AC<br><br><br>100 DPS etc.<br>075<br>050<br>025<br>000<br>000... 500 600 700 800 .... 1500 AC<br><br>Plotting this way should show a rising line as the AC increases.<br><br>If there is an AC cap somewhere the line should flatten out beyond the AC cap (if it exists)<br><br>What do you think guys? Any suggestions to make it a better test?<br><br>Also, If I face away from my attacker does my AC rating drop? If my AC rating doesn't drop I could face away from my attacker to take riposites out of the situation.<br><br><br><br> <p><center>Adex Xeda<BR> Warlord<BR> Fires of Heaven</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Swift</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 343<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/02 12:56:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScree