an.</span><hr size=1> It would be better if the mob of interest was something that no one competed for.<br><br>I wonder what kind of results you could get from attacking a red con guildtrainer NPC or similar.<br><br><br>Vindicator is a quicker spawn. It might be frequent enough for testing.<br><br><br>You know, the &quot;how hard it hits over time&quot; model might serve us better.<br><br>What you could do is every time you tank the vindicator you could turn on your log and email me the log + your AC and agility at the time you tanked it.<br><br>It would be a 3 axis plot. AC vs. average hit received vs. agility.<br><br>But this could be plotted as a data point.<br><br>If we could collect enough of these logs, we could construct a good surface plot which would show the effects of AC and agilty against the vindicator.<br><br>Of course to make it happen we'd need a lot of people emailing me logs of their fight vs. a single mob. <br><br>hmm interesting  <p><center>Adex Xeda<BR> Warlord<BR> Fires of Heaven</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Swift</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 349<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/02 3:40:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> Who am I kidding?<br><br>We'd never get enough people to submit logs.<br><br>You'd need at least 20 submissions for the surface plot to show anything useful. <p><center>Adex Xeda<BR> Warlord<BR> Fires of Heaven</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utrevurgrn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TrevurgRN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/02 3:44:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> I'd use Taskmaster Abyott in Great Divide - reasons follow.<br><br>He's always level 62.<br><br>He's almost always up, and he doesn't roam.<br><br>He's indifferent to all so you can take your time getting set up for your test.<br><br>And he actually hits for real damage (300s) compared to something like the mist panther - but doesn't hit like Yelinak so you can actually stick around quite a while with a few clerics and get a good sized log.<br><br><br> <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=104590">Ceris, 55 Warrior</A> / <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=104712">Trevurg, 54 Shaman</A></CENTER><CENTER><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=104716">Kasamar, 26 Cleric</A> / <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=104714">Veron, 24 Enchanter</A></CENTER><CENTER><A HREF="http://pub76.ezboard.com/bcascadepoint">Cascade Point</A>, <A HREF="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5024">Rodcet Nife</A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Swift</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 350<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/02 3:48:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> Maybe we're looking at this from the wrong angle.<br><br>Assume that it could be proven that past 1200ac the average damage vs. AC curve was flat or marginal vs. a certain blue con mob or PC.<br><br>Would this information be useful when making  decision to go for HP vs. AC equipment?<br><br>Personally I wonder if high AC does a lick of good vs. super mobs, I allways seem to get hit for the same amount regardless. But if I could prove that mobs you encounter during 6 man exp time are not affected by AC over 1200 then that would be useful for my decision making.<br><br> <p><center>Adex Xeda<BR> Warlord<BR> Fires of Heaven</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utrulianthescaledmofo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trulian the Scaled Mofo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/02 4:04:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Well</span><hr size=1> If you have the capability (which I am guessing you may judging on your guild), I would test ranges between 1000 and 1400 in intervals of 50. Turn NPC misses on and record several tests at the same ammount of NPC swings, look for getting hit for less, or getting hit less. A few suggestions to make would be:<br><br>If you do it in velks, pick rogue mobs and have a solid con on them. That way may be able to closely approximate the ATK rating of them by finding a high strength rogue of equal or up to +2 levels. <br><br>If you pick the panther, same thing I would say. You may also be able to approximate these by finding a cutoff point on a per-mod basis (I.E. velk spiders AC becomes useless at for instance 1200 due to low ATK or what have you). <br> <br>One thing that could be very useful to the 50+ warrior is a zone breakdown of useful AC values (Velks, Seb, Kael, ToV, WW, DN, KC, SG, all those nice little acronyms), as not all of us use our massive warrior testicles to whip out stories of tanking Vulak. And for the uber mobs I'm sure Furor has all of that calculated anyway. <br><br><br>My hypothesis for a test like this is that there is no solid cap on AC, but rather a diminishing results point. Take for instance the 900AC/Old world bit. Old world dungeon standard mobs (solusek kobolds, frogloks) seem to follow this trend, but they are also not usually 50, and the mobs that ARE 49+ in the old world always seemed to hit the same anyway. Perhaps those mobs have higher &quot;caps&quot; that we aren't seeing.<br><br>Anyhow, if it has all been said and done I apologize for rambling, though if not I hope I may be of help.<br><br><br><br>Trulian Swiftblade <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utenakha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenakha</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/02 4:06:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> Adex, as someone who has done a *lot* of ac testing here are my suggestions:<br><br>&gt;0. base 120 agility<br>&gt;1. I'll get an agility buff from a shaman. +57 agil<br><br>Just make sure its consistant throughout the entire time.  The easiest way is probably shaman buff + primal avatar to peg it at 255.<br><br>&gt;2. I'll use my primal LS until it procs and grants me 255 <br>&gt;agility. +100agil<br><br>Don't do this, you can't control procs and your results will be skewed.  Either get primal avatar or dont use primal, priceless works just fine for testing after all.<br><br>&gt;I'll repeat each AC test 3 times.<br>You don't say the duration of the test I don't think?  I suggest 10+ minutes per try.  Its long but we all know eq's rng can be flakey.<br><br>&gt;I'll stand facing the monk to allow ripostes dodging etc.<br>Why?  We don't know for sure how parry/ripostes are factored.  Are they checked for before or after hitting?  Ie a parry might indicate that a hit and then parry succeeded or it might be checked before the check to hit.  Hence this skews your results.  Have the attack happen from behind, again we are minimizing all outside factors.<br><br>&gt;I'll divide my total hitpoints by the time it took to kill me.<br>&gt;This ratio should come out as a damage per second.<br>&gt;I'll then plot the damage per second against an increasing scale of AC<br><br>Don't bother, just calculate the % chance to hit and the average damage.  Ignore all special attacks, etc.  This gives you avoidance and mitigation as you vary ac.<br><br>My suggestions (as i've said many times <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ):<br>Use a rooted mob to test.  If you don't want to use Yelinak use the VP quest guy in warslicks woods.  Don't worry about how easy/hard the mob is, figure out your results on 1 mob then you know if you should test further on other mobs.<br><br>Go to the rooted mob and take off your weapons and don't use attack.  No damage means your healers wont be summoned after all.  Just let the mob beat on your back and F9 out so you make sure you are in range the entire time.<br><br>Make sure your buffs are the same throughout, with no variation, vary your ac by changing armor (and make sure your stats stay the same as you take armor off and on).<br><br>Make sure your tests are for a sufficient duration for the test to be meaningfull.  10+ minutes is preferred.<br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7197 style="text-decoration: none">Gorlab</a> 60 Warlord<BR>Tenakha 53 Druid<BR>Officer of <a href=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org style="text-decoration: none">Keepers Of The Faith</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usolinarinnoruuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solinar Innoruuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/02 4:13:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> You said you are facing a monk? I take it this is a PC monk?<br><br>Its quite possible there is no AC limit versus PCs.<br><br>Rogue max backstab is 553 without a crit or disc versus any NPC mon, however that cap doesnt take effect versus a PC.<br>Thats why rogues love to Backstab with duelist a PC warrior who is sitting and using aggressive. They get 2X for duelist, 1.4X for aggressive, and the cap isnt in place. Pre-luclin They had backstabs near 2k this way without crits. <p><img src=http://www.ashenvendetta.com/solinar/SIG.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Swift</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/02 5:04:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> If I can face away from my target with no penalties, I can remove the effects of me riposting melee hits. <br><br>However if back attacks penalizes your AC then you're forced to face your attacker for the test. <p><center>Adex Xeda<BR> Warlord<BR> Fires of Heaven</center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=101&stop=102>6</a> </td><td align=r